<br>
Fenula knelt beside the statue of Prexus, praying. The tiny chapel in the corner of the infirmary contained statues of all the gods, for none had dominion over healing, but the Ocean Lord took central place. Taneith waited quietly in the shadows until Fenula rose.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fenula. Perhaps I am speaking out of turn, but I am worried about Echtelion. He does not seem himself. Something ails him, something that is beyond my powers perhaps. And he is stubborn and pride and would not tell me about it an any case. Do you know of what I speak?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tanieth>Tanieth</A> at: 2/5/04 6:55 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=binkafv>BinkaFV</A></span><br><font color=#A62A2A>(2/8/04 2:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=832.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chosen Spirit</span><hr size=1> Morrigane hummed a little dirge to herself happily. She loved cooking. To her, it was her second calling in life. To others, it seemed she had discovered a new way of inflicting pain and discomfort on her victims.<br>
<br>
New pledges to the guild were warned about her cooking on their first day. A few were foolish enough to think it was exaggerated. None of them had ended up in the graveyard yet, but then Fenula was a very good cleric.<br>
<br>
Morrigane jumped. A shadow seemed to detach itself from the wall. That in itself wasn’t too unusual; she was a necromancer after all. Generally she tended to sense when it was going to happen, though.<br>
<br>
“Binka, I really wish you would stop doing that!” she snapped. <br>
<br>
Binka had pretty much retired from her roguish life, but she still tended to sneak around the guild hall. She barely seemed to notice she was doing it.<br>
<br>
“Hmmm? Oh, sorry Morri. Didn’t mean to startle you.” <br>
<br>
She seemed distracted and thoughtful. That in itself was so unlike Binka it should have started alarm bells ringing, but Morrigane was too shaken to notice.<br>
<br>
“I have a job for you, a commission if you like. I need a cake made for me.”<br>
<br>
“A cake?”<br>
<br>
“Yes, a special one. A Fairy cake. With special ingredients.”<br>
<br>
From somewhere in the recesses of her chest plate, Binka pulled out a bag and dropped it on the table. The bag squirmed and there were stifled protestations coming from within.<br>
<br>
“What is it?”<br>
<br>
“Faeries.”<br>
<br>
Morrigane was astonished on two counts. Firstly both she and Binka were vegetarians. Morrigane had never cooked anything containing parts of any living creature. She knew far too much about death to ever want to consume flesh. If Binka was expecting her to cook faeries, then it must be very important.<br>
<br>
Much more importantly, if faeries were incorrectly prepared, the results were fatal. A single drop of faerie blood was enough to kill. There was no known antidote. As a result faeries were regarded as a great delicacy and were only ever prepared by Grand Master bakers.<br>
<br>
“Is this an assassination, Binka?”<br>
<br>
but Binka had melted back into the shadows, leaving the squealing and thrashing bag on the table. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=czakoriah>Czakoriah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/9/04 8:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=832.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chosen Spirit</span><hr size=1> Areli, being under the recent stress of Celo being possessed by an Iksar Enchanter named Khlsin, Neomiah being killed by Khlsin, and Echtelion being found unconscious on the floor of his room, goes off...<br>
